        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="          A.	Coherence\n          B.	Monochromaticity \n          C.	Strong unidirectionality \n          D.	Extreme brightness. \n          E.	High density of laser beam \n          F.	Narrow bandwidth  "
            android:id="@+id/textView159"
            android:layout_below="@+id/textView158"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:layout_alignRight="@+id/textView157"
            android:layout_alignEnd="@+id/textView157"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
            android:textColor="#006699" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="A.	Coherence : \n          Laser beam is perfectly coherent in nature. The emitted photon after getting triggered is exactly in phase with the incident photon. \n\nB.	Monochromaticity : \n          The laser light is almost perfectly monochromatic. \n\nC.	Extreme brightness: \n          Laser light is much more brighter and intense than that from any of the conventional source. This is due to emitted and incident photons are perfectly in phase.  "
            android:id="@+id/textView160"
            android:layout_below="@+id/textView159"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
            android:textColor="#006699" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="The solid state Ruby laser: \n Principle :  "
            android:textColor="#000000"
            android:textSize="15dp"
            android:typeface="serif"
            android:id="@+id/textView161"
            android:gravity="left|center_horizontal"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:layout_below="@+id/textView160"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="          1.	Ruby rod is surrounded by the helical Xenon photo flash lamp which provides the optical pumping to raise the chromium atoms to higher energy level. \n          2.	Much heat is given off by the flash lamp and absorbed by the ruby. \n          3.	Out of large energy produced due to flash lamp only small part of energy is used by chromium atom to get excited towards the higher energy level while the rest is converted into the heat. \n          4.	Hence to reduce the thermal vibrations in the atoms, the ruby rod is immersed in a reservoir containing a liquid nitrogen. "
            android:id="@+id/textView162"
            android:layout_below="@+id/textView161"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
            android:textColor="#006699" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="Significance of Pulse Laser :- "
            android:textColor="#000000"
            android:textSize="15dp"
            android:typeface="serif"
            android:id="@+id/textView163"
            android:gravity="left|center_horizontal"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:layout_below="@+id/textView162"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="          1.	As the flash lamp stops operating, the population of the upper level decreases very rapidly and lasing action stops till the further operation of next flash. \n          2.	As the production of laser beam totally depends upon the operation of flash so, the ruby laser is pulsed type of laser. \n          3.	During the period of operation of two flash laser output is oscillating and highly irregular function of time.\n "
            android:id="@+id/textView164"
            android:layout_below="@+id/textView163"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
            android:textColor="#006699" />
        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:text="He - Ne Laser :- "
            android:textColor="#000000"
            android:textSize="15dp"
            android:typeface="serif"
            android:id="@+id/textView165"
            android:gravity="left|center_horizontal"
            android:textStyle="bold"
            android:layout_below="@+id/textView164"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="          1.	It is the first gas laser which was operated successfully. \n          2.	He - Ne gas laser consists of a fused quartz tube which is 10 to 100 cm in length and 2 to 8 mm in the diameter. \n          3.	The tube is filled with the mixture of He and Ne gas. He is filled under the pressure of 1 mm of mercury and Ne is filled under the pressure of 0.1 mm of Mercury. \n          4.	Hence there is majority of He atom (85%) and minority of Ne atoms (15%).\n          5.	One end of the tube is closed by fully reflecting end plate while the other end has partially reflecting end plate. \n          6.	This gas laser is the commonly used low power laser, hence no cooling arrangements are required. \n          7.	Gas lasers are inexpensive, most stable and are continuous type of lasers. "
            android:id="@+id/textView166"
            android:layout_below="@+id/textView165"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
            android:textColor="#006699" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
