        <TextView
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:textAppearance="?android:attr/textAppearanceSmall"
            android:text="          1.	The band structure of an intrinsic semiconductor consists of a valence band and a conduction band separated by an energy gap Eg. \n          2.	In the normal conditions the valence band at lower energy Ev contains a large number of electrons and a few numbers of holes; while the conduction band at higher energy Ec has a few numbers of electrons. \n          3.	If a transition of electron occurs from C.B to V.B so that the electron recombines with the hole in V.B. This electron hole recombination is the basic mechanism involved in the emission of radiation. \n          4.	For the material Gallium Arsenide (GaAs) or Cadmium Selenide (CdSe) the energy released is in the optical region. \n          5.	Hence they are the suitable materials for fabrication of lasers."
            android:id="@+id/textView168"
            android:layout_alignParentStart="true"
            android:layout_below="@+id/textView167"
            android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
            android:textColor="#006699" />
